links.title: Nancy Wake
links.description: Nancy Grace Augusta Wake AC, GM (30 August 1912 - 7 August 2011) served as a British Special Operations Executive agent during the later part of World War II. She became a leading figure in the maquis groups of the French Resistance and was one of the Allies' most decorated servicewomen of the war.
